<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.logging.ILogTarget.Deleter" Title="Deleter structure" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.ILogTarget">ILogTarget</PageRef> ->
    Deleter
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Declaration">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[struct Deleter;]]></Code>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>Deleter</TypeRef> structure is the custom deleter used by <TypeRef>ILogTarget::unique_ptr</TypeRef>. It destroys a target by calling the virtual <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.ILogTarget.Delete">Delete</PageRef> method on the object.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
      Applications normally interact with this structure indirectly when transferring targets to <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.LogManager.AddLogTarget">LogManager.AddLogTarget</PageRef>.
    </Paragraph>
  </Section>
